CloudWatch mainly for monitoring, alerting, and troubleshooting production issues.
worked with metrics, logs, alarms, and dashboards to ensure application availability and performance.

1. Monitoring EC2 & Application Health
Monitored EC2 CPU, memory (via custom metrics), disk usage
Created CloudWatch Alarms:
CPU > 70% → trigger alert
Status check failed → immediate alert
Integrated alarms with SNS to notify team

I configured CloudWatch alarms for EC2 metrics and integrated them 
with SNS to send alerts when thresholds were breached.

2. Log Monitoring & Debugging
Enabled CloudWatch Logs Agent
Pushed:
Application logs
Nginx/Apache logs
Used Log Insights to debug issues

Production issue where the application was failing intermittently. 
I used CloudWatch Logs Insights to filter error patterns and identified a 
database connection timeout issue.

3. Auto Scaling Integration
Connected CloudWatch alarms to Auto Scaling Group
Example:
CPU > 70% → scale out
CPU < 30% → scale in
CloudWatch metrics to trigger scaling policies, 
ensuring the application handled traffic automatically

